
admin.php:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
by Don Moore <bboy@bboy.net> (http://mydns.bboy.net)
and David Phillips <david@acz.org> (http://david.acz.org)

A fully functional web interface to the MyDNS data.  To use, copy
admin.php to your http-space and edit the configuration variables at the
top of the file.  You will obviously need PHP installed and configured
in order to use this script.  See http://www.php.net/ for PHP help.


alias.patch:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
by David Phillips <david@acz.org> (http://david.acz.org)

A patch to add functionality for server side aliasing for A records.
Aliased records are returned to the client as normal A records: the client
will not know that any translation took place.  These work anytime an A
record is needed, such as when providing additional records for NS or MX
records.  For more info, see "README.alias".

To install, configure mydns with "--enable-alias" and build.


create_domain.pl:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
by Gerard de Brieder <smeevil@meladicta.com>

A Perl script to add a minimal functioning domain entry.


MyDNS.pm
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
by Allen Bettilyon <allen@bettilyon.net>

An object based interface to the MyDNS DB information.


mydns.redhat
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
by Ari Pollak <ajp@aripollak.com>

A SysV-style init script for use with RedHat (and possibly other RPM-based
systems).


mydns.solaris
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
by Fernando Durango <fernando@secret.org>

MyDNS startup script for Solaris.


stats.php:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
by Don Moore <bboy@bboy.net> (http://mydns.bboy.net)

An example of a command-line PHP script that captures the query log lines
from "mydns --verbose" and does something with the data.


dnsmanager/
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
by Dan Caescu <dan.caescu@multitel.net>

A modern web-based DNS management interface for MyDNS with full Cloudflare
integration. Built with React/TypeScript frontend and Node.js/Express backend.

Features:
  - Complete SOA and Resource Record management
  - Cloudflare zones, DNS records, and load balancer synchronization
  - User management with role-based access control (superadmin/admin/user)
  - API token system for programmatic access
  - Two-factor authentication (2FA) support
  - Support ticket system with screenshot capture and email notifications
  - Real-time health monitoring for Cloudflare load balancer pools

Installation requires Node.js and npm. See dnsmanager/README.md for detailed
setup instructions including database migrations, environment configuration,
and deployment steps.


sync_cloudflare_records.py:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
by Dan Caescu <dan.caescu@multitel.net>

Synchronizes Cloudflare accounts, zones, and DNS records into the local
MyDNS database. This script mirrors Cloudflare data to local MySQL tables
for unified management and can be executed from cron for periodic syncing.

Reads configuration from:
  - /etc/mydns/cloudflare.ini (Cloudflare credentials and account IDs)
  - /etc/mydns/mydns.conf (database connection details with failover support)

Requires: pymysql, requests


ACL_USER_GUIDE.md:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
by Dan Caescu <dan.caescu@multitel.net>

Complete user guide for MyDNS Enhanced ACL System for DNS UPDATE operations.
Covers configuration, common use cases, security best practices, monitoring,
troubleshooting, and migration from the old soa.update_acl system.

Features documented:
  - Zone-specific access control with IP/CIDR restrictions
  - TSIG authentication integration
  - Granular permissions (add/delete/update separately)
  - Complete audit logging
  - Priority-based ACL rules

See also: dnsupdate-schema.sql for database schema and SQL examples.


sync_pools_direct.py:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
by Dan Caescu <dan.caescu@multitel.net>

Fetches Cloudflare load balancer pools and origins directly from the
Cloudflare API and synchronizes them to the local database. Updates pool
configurations, origin health status, and associated metadata.

Reads configuration from /etc/mydns/cloudflare.ini and /etc/mydns/mydns.conf.

Requires: pymysql, requests


check_pool_cf.py:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
by Dan Caescu <dan.caescu@multitel.net>

Diagnostic utility to query and display Cloudflare load balancer pool data
directly from the Cloudflare API. Useful for debugging pool configurations
and verifying API connectivity.

Edit the script to set EMAIL, API_KEY, ACCOUNT_ID, and POOL_ID before use.

Requires: requests


check_mydns.py:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
by Dan Caescu <dan.caescu@multitel.net>

NRPE/Icinga monitoring plugin for MyDNS. Verifies that all configured
database hosts are reachable, the mydns daemon process is running, and
optionally tests DNS query responses using dig.

Example NRPE command:
  command[check_mydns]=/usr/local/lib/nagios/plugins/check_mydns.py \
      --config /etc/mydns/mydns.conf \
      --query-name example.com --query-type SOA --server 127.0.0.1

Returns standard Nagios exit codes (OK/WARNING/CRITICAL/UNKNOWN).


